    "The code clone detection process begins by modeling the semantics of the source code.",
    "To achieve this goal, diverse program representations such as tokens, ASTs, CFGs, data flow graphs (DFGs), and PDGs are being used to learn program features.Various deep learning models, such as CodeBERT, GraphCodeBERT, GNN, graph attention network, CNN, GCN, ASTNN, tree-based convolutional neural network (TBCNN), recursive autoencoders (RAE), RNN, recursive neural network (RvNN), LSTM, have been used.These studies have achieved higher recall and better precision than the best classical approaches.",
    "Code representation learning for clone detectionThe studies in Table 10 [248,261,268,275,276,278,280,281,283,[285][286][287][288][289][290][291][292][293][294][295] focus on learning source code representation, so as to automatically capture the syntactic and semantic information from source code.Then the embedding is applied to code clone detection, code classification tasks, etc.",
    "Code similarities can be learned from diverse representations of the code, such as identifiers, tokens, ASTs, CFGs, DFGs, and bytecode."
